: The government has given additional charge of Principal Secretary (Industries) to G. Kamala Vardhana Rao, who currently functions as Principal Secretary (Tourism).It has also appointed former Kerala Veterinary and Animal Sciences University Vice Chancellor B. Asok as Secretary, Sainik Welfare, with additional charge of Official Languages Department. Former Kerala State Civil Supplies Corporation (Supplyco) managing director A.T. James has been appointed Rural Development Commissioner with additional charge as Mission Director, Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme (MGNREGS). S. Venkitesapathy is the new Supplyco Managing Director.The government has also appointed K.V. Mohankumar as Director, Higher Secondary Education, with additional charge of Malabar Cultural Academy. K.N. Sathish, who was the Director, Higher Secondary Education, would be appointed Additional Secretary, Planning and Economic Affairs, an official press note said here on Friday.